-- Prelios May Need 150 Million-Euro Capital Boost, Repubblica Says
-- B y   E l i s a   M a r t i n u z z i
-- 2012-08-12T10:43:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-12/prelios-may-need-150-million-euro-capital-boost-repubblica-says.html
Prelios SpA (PRS)  may need to raise as
much as 150 million euros ($184 million) in capital after
writedowns that will lead to a loss of about 120 million euros
for the first half, la Repubblica reported, without saying how
it obtained the information.  Fortress Investment Group LLC (FIG)  and Massimo Caputi are
considering separate bids for Prelios and may make formal offers
next month, according to the  daily newspaper .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisa Martinuzzi in Milan at 
 emartinuzzi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at 
